author: @sojournerlies3848
text: It's jarring as a new viewer to hear you harp so much on jobs not paying to upskill their employees as I just watched one of your videos yesterday highlighting tuition reimbursement as a benefit to keep an eye out for when applying. _________ If you're going to position yourself as above drama, then... be above it... You don't actually get points for claiming to be above drama and having no issues with someone, when you actively engage in with what you believe to be drama and spend a whole video being passive aggressive.  This contention definitely feels like a thinly veiled attempt at driving engagement. Which is kind of sad but on brand for 2021 influencer culture.   It was just weird to hear you say you love this guy like a brother and have no issue with him, and then in the very next breath say that he stole a video topic that you had not yet published - with a straight face. It was surprisingly accurate foreshadowing of the next eleven and a half minutes of judging his tabs, his video editing, and... his pull ups...  Not sure if yall see the Google Certificate as something that will significantly expand your niches viewership and are now trying to claim the biggest share of new viewers, but if so, I guarantee you aggy videos like this aren't going to keep viewers coming back. Fix it.
